# Trivy vulnerability waivers for the Ancora Health backend image (S-76).
#
# Policy: the image must scan clean of HIGH/CRITICAL findings. The runtime stage
# is gcr.io/distroless/static-debian12:nonroot — it carries only the static Go
# binary, ca-certificates, tzdata and /etc/passwd, so the OS-package attack
# surface is essentially nil. Remaining findings, if any, come from Go module
# dependencies and are fixed by bumping the module (go get -u) — prefer a fix
# over a waiver.
#
# Add a waiver ONLY with: the CVE id, the affected module, why it is not
# exploitable in this image, and a review date. An unexplained id here is a bug.
#
# Format: one CVE id per line (optionally `CVE-ID exp:YYYY-MM-DD`).
#
# --- Active waivers ---
# (none — the image currently scans clean; see docs/container.md for how to scan)
